11. Risks and Mitigations

11.1 Technical Risks

Risk 1: Computational Complexity

· Mitigation: Progressive computation, layer-specific optimization
· Fallback: Minimal viable system mode

Risk 2: Training Data Limitations

· Mitigation: Synthetic data generation, continuous data collection
· Fallback: Rule-based systems with learning disabled

Risk 3: Verification Challenges

· Mitigation: Formal methods, continuous verification
· Fallback: Human-in-the-loop verification

11.2 Ethical Risks

Risk 1: Value Drift

· Mitigation: Continuous alignment monitoring, periodic recalibration
· Fallback: Purpose lock mechanisms

Risk 2: Unintended Consequences

· Mitigation: Foresight simulation, impact assessment
· Fallback: Restraint protocols, human oversight

Risk 3: Misuse Potential

· Mitigation: Built-in constraints, use-case validation
· Fallback: Capability limitation modes

11.3 Social Risks

Risk 1: Dependency Creation

· Mitigation: Autonomy encouragement, skill development support
· Fallback: Usage limitation features

Risk 2: Wisdom Standardization

· Mitigation: Multi-cultural wisdom sources, perspective diversity
· Fallback: Cultural context awareness

Risk 3: Access Inequality

· Mitigation: Open access components, tiered service model
· Fallback: Essential services freely available

